-- Barnier Sees No `Serious Breach' With Eurostar Rail Purchase, FT Reports
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2010-10-19T02:00:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/barnier-sees-no-serious-breach-with-eurostar-rail-purchase-ft-reports.html
Michel Barnier , the European Union
financial services commissioner, has written to  Alstom SA  saying
he “could not ascertain any serious breach of the EU’s public
procurement rules” regarding Eurostar Group Ltd.’s plan to buy
10  Siemens AG  trains, the Financial Times reported, citing
European Commission officials.  Alstom had written to Barnier to express concern about the
plan, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ben Martin  in London at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net . 